00:53:27,965 --> 00:53:29,278
Very fast.

497
00:53:29,841 --> 00:53:32,635
I didn't think they'd get here that quick.

498
00:53:32,967 --> 00:53:35,952
And boys, let's go have some fun.

499
00:54:08,146 --> 00:54:11,040
Kate, I don't know
what we're gonna be up against in there...

500
00:54:11,140 --> 00:54:14,719
- so I'm gonna need you to stay in the car.
- Okay.

501
00:54:41,185 --> 00:54:42,296
West side, report.

502
00:54:43,061 --> 00:54:44,238
West side, clear.

503
00:54:44,805 --> 00:54:47,733
- Thomas, assessment.
- They've been tipped-off.

504
00:56:21,026 --> 00:56:22,990
Just like the fourth of July.

505
00:56:24,087 --> 00:56:25,399
Okay, hero.

506
00:56:27,016 --> 00:56:28,553
Present for you.

507
00:56:59,890 --> 00:57:01,337
Bomb! Get out!

508
00:57:25,624 --> 00:57:28,744
Hey! Come on!

509
00:57:28,850 --> 00:57:30,588
- Help me!
- Open up!

510
00:57:31,383 --> 00:57:34,109
Oh, I'm burned! I'm burning down!

511
00:57:56,130 --> 00:57:57,308
Thomas!

512
00:58:39,864 --> 00:58:42,815
- What the hell happened?
- You better buckle up.

513
00:58:53,094 --> 00:58:55,091
Son of a bitch.

514
00:59:25,079 --> 00:59:27,211
Here, have this on your conscience, then.

515
00:59:31,069 --> 00:59:32,808
Please don't hit him!

516
00:59:39,361 --> 00:59:41,492
Car. Car. Car!

517
01:00:00,290 --> 01:00:02,747
Bus. Thomas, there's a bus.

518
01:00:03,549 --> 01:00:05,423
Okay, you see the kids?

519
01:00:11,282 --> 01:00:12,920
It's gonna be on your head.

520
01:00:14,540 --> 01:00:17,557
Thomas, stop! Thomas, bus! Stop!

521
01:00:21,911 --> 01:00:22,988
Stop! It's a bus!

522
01:00:23,293 --> 01:00:24,404
So what're you gonna do?

523
01:00:25,893 --> 01:00:28,418
There are children on it! Stop! Let him go!

524
01:00:32,376 --> 01:00:34,339
Well, you lose, you son of a bitch.

525
01:00:42,544 --> 01:00:45,405
- Bang!
- Bye-bye.

526
01:00:51,988 --> 01:00:53,896
Thank you. Thank you.

527
01:01:07,488 --> 01:01:10,708
- You might want to stay here.
- What?

528
01:01:15,617 --> 01:01:16,660
What?

529
01:01:25,554 --> 01:01:28,808
What in the... This is not good.

530
01:01:33,419 --> 01:01:35,584
- What are you doing?
- I owe him one.

531
01:01:35,690 --> 01:01:38,708
Not good. This is not good!
This is not good!

532
01:01:39,244 --> 01:01:40,288
Shit!

533
01:01:58,331 --> 01:01:59,508
Stevens.

534
01:02:00,141 --> 01:02:02,900
Miss Crawford,
would you excuse us, please?

535
01:02:03,332 --> 01:02:05,666
What did I tell you this morning?
Give me two days, did I not?

536
01:02:05,767 --> 01:02:08,168
- lt was my idea, sir.
- Shut up. Did I not say that this morning?

537
01:02:08,268 --> 01:02:10,725
- It's all my idea, sir.
- Really? Then how come you knew...

538
01:02:10,835 --> 01:02:13,068
that the assassin's accomplice
would be in that warehouse?

539
01:02:13,172 --> 01:02:14,978
- 'Cause I told him, sir.
- That's right.

540
01:02:15,080 --> 01:02:17,672
- And he's only a suspect.
- What are our losses?

541
01:02:18,207 --> 01:02:21,191
Two dead, two wounded,
one critically burned and in lC.

542
01:02:21,958 --> 01:02:25,998
- ls he gonna pull through?
- Yes, thanks to Thomas, he has a chance.

543
01:02:29,724 --> 01:02:32,316
Off the record. Off the record.

544
01:02:33,608 --> 01:02:37,984
You two... Three,
did a hell of a job out there today.

545
01:02:39,071 --> 01:02:41,371
Okay, what's the deal with this guy,
the suspect...

546
01:02:41,472 --> 01:02:42,650
or "not the suspect"?

547
01:02:42,756 --> 01:02:44,664
Still unconscious and in critical condition.

548
01:02:44,763 --> 01:02:46,143
All right. Well, we'll need him alive.

549
01:02:46,244 --> 01:02:48,700
- Call me when he can talk.
- Yes, sir.

550
01:02:48,909 --> 01:02:50,581
- Miss Crawford.
- Mr. Stevens.

551
01:02:50,687 --> 01:02:53,446
- Can I speak with you, please?
- Of course.

552
01:02:55,820 --> 01:02:59,601
Wonder Woman.
Remarkable what you did today, thank you.

553
01:02:59,703 --> 01:03:00,780
I appreciate that.

554
01:03:00,888 --> 01:03:02,661
And you have an article to write,
do you not?

555
01:03:02,764 --> 01:03:04,795
Yes, and a very good one, at that.

556
01:03:05,232 --> 01:03:09,339
Now, since you're so intimately involved
in all of this...

557
01:03:10,562 --> 01:03:14,736
could you spare the details to the public,
until I get to the bottom of it?

558
01:03:15,565 --> 01:03:17,595
The public has a right to know.

559
01:03:17,704 --> 01:03:21,586
I'm not ordering you. I wouldn't, I couldn't.
I'm asking you.

560
01:03:23,134 --> 01:03:26,949
And in return, I will give you
an exclusive one-on-one with me.

561
01:03:27,544 --> 01:03:29,507
- Before anyone else?
- Yes.

562
01:03:30,208 --> 01:03:32,014
- Full disclosure?
- Yes.

563
01:03:32,446 --> 01:03:33,792
- Deal.
- Deal.

564
01:03:41,035 --> 01:03:44,783
- What did he say?
- Well, overall, I'd say it went pretty well.

565
01:03:45,412 --> 01:03:47,679
For now. Let's get out of here.

566
01:03:49,888 --> 01:03:51,986
Hey, take my car.

567
01:03:52,651 --> 01:03:55,479
I'll find another ride. Look after it, will you?

568
01:03:55,581 --> 01:03:57,027
Thanks, Brian.

569
01:04:22,630 --> 01:04:23,841
This way.

570
01:04:24,046 --> 01:04:25,123
Pull!

571
01:04:31,121 --> 01:04:32,164
Pull!

572
01:04:34,444 --> 01:04:36,150
Great shot, General.

573
01:04:37,637 --> 01:04:39,207
Thank you, Alex.

574
01:04:40,599 --> 01:04:45,267
I didn't realize
you were bringing a journalist with you.

575
01:04:45,469 --> 01:04:46,512
Sir.

576
01:04:48,233 --> 01:04:51,128
- Miss Crawford. No offense.
- None taken, General.

577
01:04:51,227 --> 01:04:53,561
We're working together on this one, sir.

578
01:04:54,090 --> 01:04:56,525
Really? What you got for me?

579
01:04:56,855 --> 01:04:58,852
His name is Philip Keefer.

580
01:05:01,132 --> 01:05:03,230
I put him in the hospital yesterday.

581
01:05:06,858 --> 01:05:08,799
His name is Jack Baldwin.

582
01:05:09,360 --> 01:05:11,165
- Not Keefer?
- No.

583
01:05:12,223 --> 01:05:15,443
He's a former contract employee for the ClA.

584
01:05:17,850 --> 01:05:19,522
You mean contract killer?

585
01:05:21,206 --> 01:05:24,426
Ten years ago,
he was a deputy director's man.

586
01:05:24,530 --> 01:05:27,615
He virtually ran the lSG.

587
01:05:28,018 --> 01:05:29,196
General?

588
01:05:30,914 --> 01:05:33,506
Who was the deputy director
of operations then?

589
01:05:34,271 --> 01:05:35,741
Vaughn Stevens.

590
01:05:36,903 --> 01:05:38,081
Stevens?

591
01:05:39,174 --> 01:05:43,347
I know where you're headed with this,
but I'll stake my reputation.

592
01:05:43,583 --> 01:05:47,229
The ClA had nothing to do
with the assassination of the President.

593
01:05:47,335 --> 01:05:50,588
As a matter of fact,
the President was very close to the ClA.

594
01:05:51,613 --> 01:05:53,813
What's curious about all this is...

595
01:05:55,200 --> 01:05:56,378
Baldwin.

596
01:05:57,766 --> 01:06:00,986
I mean, even with him in the picture,
there's no motive.

597
01:06:02,209 --> 01:06:05,362
Question is, who would gain the most...

598
01:06:07,079 --> 01:06:09,244
by the death of the President?

599
01:06:13,168 --> 01:06:15,232
Like to stay for breakfast?

600
01:06:16,195 --> 01:06:20,369
That's very generous of you, sir,
but I think it's best we get going.

601
01:06:21,723 --> 01:06:23,956
- All right.
- Thank you again, General.

602
01:06:24,982 --> 01:06:27,641
Remember, the deeper you dig...

603
01:06:28,766 --> 01:06:31,133
the less you're gonna like what you find.

604
01:07:01,279 --> 01:07:02,456
...understand that, right?

605
01:07:02,562 --> 01:07:05,815
Of course I understand.
I'm in the middle of it as much as you are.

606
01:07:06,709 --> 01:07:08,245
Why didn't you try calling me or something?

607
01:07:08,354 --> 01:07:09,801
- I will, I'll call you Thursday.
- Okay.

608
01:07:09,900 --> 01:07:11,145
- Okay?
- Okay.

609
01:07:11,249 --> 01:07:12,820
Until then, stiff upper lip. All right?

610
01:07:16,449 --> 01:07:19,838
- Miss Crawford, aren't you here a bit early?
- lt was light traffic.

611
01:07:20,365 --> 01:07:21,678
Sorry to have surprised you.

612
01:07:21,781 --> 01:07:24,080
- Who was that?
- No one important.

613
01:07:25,597 --> 01:07:26,775
Really?

614
01:07:27,242 --> 01:07:30,889
'Cause it looked like Judy Fincher
from WestLake Publishing.

615
01:07:31,422 --> 01:07:35,001
You wouldn't be thinking about reneging
on our promised interview, would you?

616
01:07:35,108 --> 01:07:37,071
I had heard that your editor
pulled the story. So?

617
01:07:37,181 --> 01:07:38,425
- Really, you heard that?
- Yeah.

618
01:07:38,530 --> 01:07:41,055
That's odd, I didn't hear that. Who told you?

619
01:07:41,360 --> 01:07:43,301
Surely, you of all people should know...

620
01:07:43,400 --> 01:07:45,890
that the grapevine in this town
reaches a lot of walls.

621
01:07:46,000 --> 01:07:49,354
Well, did the grapevine also tell you
that I'm a freelancer?

622
01:07:49,456 --> 01:07:51,329
So I can give my story
to anyone who wants it.

623
01:07:51,430 --> 01:07:54,224
Let me just make this as clear to you
as I possibly can, Miss Crawford.

624
01:07:54,326 --> 01:07:57,546
I am not at liberty to discuss Philip Keefer.
My hands are tied.

625
01:07:57,649 --> 01:07:59,646
- That will not happen.
- That's okay.

626
01:07:59,756 --> 01:08:03,200
Because I'm actually going to change
the angle of the article...

627
01:08:03,309 --> 01:08:05,340
- and do it on Jack Baldwin.
- Good.

628
01:08:06,271 --> 01:08:08,537
I'm sorry, I have to take this.

629
01:08:08,641 --> 01:08:11,828
Hello? Yes. I can be right there.

630
01:08:11,931 --> 01:08:13,434
Okay. Bye-bye.

631
01:08:13,544 --> 01:08:17,515
- I'm so sorry. Can I reschedule?
- Of course.

632
01:08:17,625 --> 01:08:18,904
Thank you.

633
01:08:19,171 --> 01:08:20,741
- Hi, Brian.
- Kate.

634
01:08:22,593 --> 01:08:25,813
- What did she want?
- Nothing. Just being a reporter.

635
01:09:15,739 --> 01:09:17,904
- Hello.
- It's Agent Thomas.

636
01:09:18,208 --> 01:09:20,900
Alex. How you doing?

637
01:09:21,005 --> 01:09:22,082
I'm doing.

638
01:09:22,486 --> 01:09:26,099
- I'm really sorry about everything.
- Yeah, me, too.

639
01:09:29,692 --> 01:09:31,229
You meant a lot to him.

640
01:09:31,338 --> 01:09:34,423
- He was gonna divorce her and marry you.
- I know.

641
01:09:35,122 --> 01:09:37,522
I just want the President to be...

642
01:09:37,722 --> 01:09:40,583
remembered as a good President and not...

643
01:09:41,013 --> 01:09:42,549
Still protecting him, huh?

644
01:09:43,580 --> 01:09:45,150
Well, don't worry, Agent Thomas.

645
01:09:45,257 --> 01:09:47,198
What happened between me
and the President...

646
01:09:47,298 --> 01:09:49,957
will stay between me and the President.

647
01:09:51,313 --> 01:09:53,344
No one else needs to know.

648
01:09:53,781 --> 01:09:54,958
Thanks.

649
01:09:55,525 --> 01:09:58,184
- lf you ever need anything...
- I won't.

650
01:09:58,881 --> 01:10:00,059
Thanks.

651
01:10:35,113 --> 01:10:37,638
Alex, what a surprise.

652
01:10:40,444 --> 01:10:42,441
You never forget a thing, do you?

653
01:10:42,945 --> 01:10:46,849
- What have you been up to lately?
- Oh, just working on my boat.

654
01:10:47,354 --> 01:10:50,080
- And you?
- Working on my art.

655
01:10:51,205 --> 01:10:52,943
I'm nearly finished.

656
01:10:53,673 --> 01:10:55,906
Been waiting to show it to you.

657
01:11:00,024 --> 01:11:01,662
What do you think?

658
01:11:08,382 --> 01:11:10,940
I think a lot of things, to be honest.

659
01:11:12,069 --> 01:11:14,930
Like maybe there wasn't
just one lone gunman.

660
01:11:15,885 --> 01:11:17,455
What do you mean?

661
01:11:18,354 --> 01:11:20,687
We have a suspect in the hospital.

662
01:11:20,789 --> 01:11:23,874
Whatever is going on,
we'll find out soon enough.

663
01:11:29,411 --> 01:11:31,285
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

664
01:11:32,537 --> 01:11:34,074
It is beautiful.

665
01:11:38,986 --> 01:11:40,591
You're too close.

666
01:11:43,429 --> 01:11:45,034
You can't see it.

667
01:11:48,333 --> 01:11:51,059
You have to see it
from the right perspective.

668
01:12:03,437 --> 01:12:04,682
Try mine.

669
01:12:20,220 --> 01:12:23,204
Wow. That is truly amazing.

670
01:12:23,642 --> 01:12:26,436
So, are any of these powdered?

671
01:12:28,348 --> 01:12:31,826
- Have I ever brought you anything else?
- No.

672
01:12:42,202 --> 01:12:44,008
Take care of yourself.

673
01:12:57,339 --> 01:12:59,998
- Here you go.
- Yeah. Thanks a lot.

674
01:13:13,860 --> 01:13:15,329
Perfect timing.

675
01:13:23,765 --> 01:13:25,044
Thank you.

676
01:13:38,113 --> 01:13:39,918
Who won the last game?

677
01:13:43,904 --> 01:13:45,811
Are those framed checks?

678
01:13:47,195 --> 01:13:48,238
Yeah.

679
01:14:22,439 --> 01:14:23,976
I'm sorry, Alex.

680
01:14:30,239 --> 01:14:31,282
Yeah.

681
01:14:59,856 --> 01:15:01,886
You know what burns my ass?

682
01:15:02,224 --> 01:15:06,163
The fact that Baldwin is still in the hospital
and he's still alive.

683
01:15:23,252 --> 01:15:26,147
Thomas, why are you watching
that morbid tape?

684
01:15:26,839 --> 01:15:29,924
We confiscated tapes
from five different cameras.

685
01:15:30,822 --> 01:15:33,088
I'm sure I'm missing something.

686
01:15:36,844 --> 01:15:40,625
- What is that?
- Well it's... My cell phone is dying.

687
01:15:41,944 --> 01:15:44,839
So, I went to interview Stevens today...

688
01:15:46,057 --> 01:15:49,939
and I saw the publisher, Judy Fincher,
coming out of his office.

689
01:15:50,040 --> 01:15:52,496
I don't know what that's all about.

690
01:15:53,066 --> 01:15:55,433
But I told him
that I was changing the angle of my story...

691
01:15:55,535 --> 01:15:57,992
from Philip Keefer to Jack Baldwin.

692
01:15:58,891 --> 01:16:01,225
And I could tell it shook him up.

693
01:16:09,159 --> 01:16:11,459
Wait, stop. Pause it. Stop.

694
01:16:13,667 --> 01:16:15,204
Do you see that?

695
01:16:16,498 --> 01:16:20,638
- Detimore is so close to Stevens.
- Yeah, close enough to get a gun.

696
01:16:20,742 --> 01:16:23,603
Call the police, the FBl, somebody,
we have to arrest him.

697
01:16:23,704 --> 01:16:28,136
It's not enough to arrest him,
but it's definitely enough to confront him.

698
01:16:28,936 --> 01:16:30,249
- Brian.
- Yeah?

699
01:16:30,351 --> 01:16:33,044
- Find out where Stevens is right away.
- Okay, call you back.

700
01:16:33,412 --> 01:16:34,623
Let's go.

701
01:16:35,354 --> 01:16:36,666
You coming?

702
01:16:38,183 --> 01:16:39,158
No.

703
01:16:40,059 --> 01:16:43,773
I can't go with you.
We're the only two that know about this.

704
01:16:45,489 --> 01:16:49,203
If you don't come back,
I'm the only one who knows the truth.

705
01:16:55,690 --> 01:16:58,674
Well, then,
I guess the tape's in good hands...

706
01:17:00,823 --> 01:17:02,001
partner.

707
01:17:09,610 --> 01:17:11,146
- Martin.
- Yeah.

708
01:17:11,256 --> 01:17:13,253
- He's at home.
- How do you know he's there?

709
01:17:13,361 --> 01:17:14,831
Well, you know Stevens.

710
01:17:14,941 --> 01:17:18,520
Whenever the wife is out of town,
things get busy at the mansion.

711
01:17:18,627 --> 01:17:20,332
Okay, I'm on my way.

712
01:17:49,494 --> 01:17:50,841
Vaughn, sir?

713
01:17:57,853 --> 01:17:59,458
It's Agent Thomas.

714
01:18:00,749 --> 01:18:02,162
Are you here?

715
01:18:12,760 --> 01:18:15,621
Vaughn? It's Agent Thomas.

716
01:18:24,277 --> 01:18:25,421
Vaughn?

717
01:18:39,383 --> 01:18:42,468
- Alex, everything all right?
- ln here.

718
01:18:51,229 --> 01:18:52,340
Jesus.

719
01:18:59,357 --> 01:19:01,096
Looks like a suicide.

720
01:19:02,023 --> 01:19:04,423
Or someone wants us to think that.

721
01:19:06,498 --> 01:19:09,393
When I pulled up,
I saw a woman driving away.

722
01:19:09,493 --> 01:19:12,320
- Get forensics up here.
- I'll make the call.

723
01:19:18,114 --> 01:19:20,976
- Hello.
- Kate, Jesus Christ, where've you been?

724
01:19:21,142 --> 01:19:22,320
- No calls, no fax.
- I know.

725
01:19:22,425 --> 01:19:23,704
I even told you an e-mail would work.

726
01:19:23,808 --> 01:19:26,175
Yes. I'm sending you an e-mail right now
with the whole story.

727
01:19:26,276 --> 01:19:27,353
Yeah, right.

728
01:19:27,460 --> 01:19:30,781
Okay, listen, this thing is so much bigger
than any of us thought.

729
01:19:30,882 --> 01:19:35,315
Okay, every lead that I've gone to is dead.
And I almost joined them.

730
01:19:35,424 --> 01:19:37,589
- What?
- So, I'm typing it right now.

731
01:19:37,694 --> 01:19:39,007
You should get it momentarily.

732
01:19:39,702 --> 01:19:42,227
Listen, I gotta go.
My phone is running out of juice.

733
01:19:42,335 --> 01:19:44,735
- No, don't hang... Don't.
- Okay, bye.

734
01:19:47,864 --> 01:19:49,602
There were several fluids on his shorts...

735
01:19:49,706 --> 01:19:52,365
but there were no other prints
found at the scene, other than his.

736
01:19:52,470 --> 01:19:56,083
Stevens was murdered.
No way it was a suicide.

737
01:19:56,946 --> 01:19:58,943
Some woman fled the scene.

738
01:20:01,421 --> 01:20:02,868
Wait a minute.

739
01:20:03,133 --> 01:20:05,927
Crawford said she saw him earlier today
with Judy Fincher...

740
01:20:06,028 --> 01:20:07,992
some well-known publisher.

741
01:20:08,135 --> 01:20:11,422
I remember her now.
She was with Stevens at the wake.

742
01:20:13,268 --> 01:20:14,715
- Janice.
- Yes?

743
01:20:14,815 --> 01:20:17,866
Find out what you can on a Judith Fincher.

744
01:20:18,072 --> 01:20:20,900
- F-I-N-C-H-E-R.
- Right away, Alex.

745
01:20:23,963 --> 01:20:25,568
All right. So what do we have?

746
01:20:25,674 --> 01:20:29,489
Detimore is dying of cancer,
hired to kill the President.

747
01:20:30,018 --> 01:20:31,622
Gives the money to his family.

748
01:20:31,729 --> 01:20:34,556
Baldwin comes in
to clean up any loose ends.

749
01:20:34,823 --> 01:20:38,143
Videotape shows
that he probably got the gun from Stevens.

750
01:20:38,245 --> 01:20:40,904
Not to mention a fake press pass.

751
01:20:42,622 --> 01:20:45,247
Stevens would be the perfect one
to engineer it.

752
01:20:45,353 --> 01:20:48,865
Stevens used to handle Baldwin.
Probably got him to do the dirty work.

753
01:20:48,973 --> 01:20:50,510
All the evidence points to Stevens...

754
01:20:50,618 --> 01:20:53,277
making him
the only real loose end to tie up.

755
01:20:53,383 --> 01:20:54,829
Yeah, but why?

756
01:20:54,962 --> 01:20:56,925
What does he have to gain?

757
01:20:57,694 --> 01:21:01,632
Money? Power? He had plenty of both.

758
01:21:01,971 --> 01:21:03,643
Well, why do men do anything?

759
01:21:05,328 --> 01:21:08,346
- Women.
- Right, women.

760
01:21:09,671 --> 01:21:12,196
- What do you got?
- Nothing out of the ordinary.

761
01:21:12,305 --> 01:21:15,132
Graduated Yale Law,
went straight into publishing.

762
01:21:15,233 --> 01:21:16,702
Pretty standard bio.

763
01:21:16,813 --> 01:21:19,640
I printed out some pictures
and a complete business history.

764
01:21:19,741 --> 01:21:22,175
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

765
01:21:22,439 --> 01:21:23,483
Here.

766
01:21:43,008 --> 01:21:45,408
Martin here. What?

767
01:21:45,508 --> 01:21:47,471
Took down two agents before he escaped.

768
01:21:47,582 --> 01:21:49,287
We need you over here right away.

769
01:21:49,391 --> 01:21:51,130
I'll be right there.

770
01:21:53,110 --> 01:21:55,376
Baldwin killed two agents at the hospital
and disappeared.

771
01:21:55,480 --> 01:21:57,421
- And they had the place surrounded.
- Let's go.

772
01:21:57,519 --> 01:21:59,819
If he manages to escape
and finds out that Stevens is dead...

773
01:21:59,922 --> 01:22:01,301
he's gonna come after you and Crawford.

774
01:22:01,403 --> 01:22:03,928
Head over to the hospital.
I'll call if I need backup.

775
01:22:21,114 --> 01:22:22,684
Answer the phone.

776
01:22:27,136 --> 01:22:28,146
Hello.

777
01:22:28,255 --> 01:22:29,927
Is everything all right?

778
01:22:30,033 --> 01:22:31,076
Yeah, everything's fine, why?

779
01:22:31,184 --> 01:22:32,395
Baldwin just escaped.

780
01:22:33,258 --> 01:22:34,828
What? Thomas, I can't...

781
01:22:34,935 --> 01:22:36,046
Hello?

782
01:22:40,727 --> 01:22:41,771
Shit.

783
01:22:57,543 --> 01:22:58,653
Hello.

784
01:23:12,779 --> 01:23:14,092
Flashlight.

785
01:23:29,496 --> 01:23:31,066
Hello, beautiful.

786
01:23:31,471 --> 01:23:33,636
Help me understand something.

787
01:23:33,807 --> 01:23:36,332
With all the horrible things
going on in the world...

788
01:23:36,440 --> 01:23:38,438
why do you concentrate...

789
01:23:38,809 --> 01:23:42,029
on a man who's not worth his weight
in fertilizer, huh?

790
01:23:42,133 --> 01:23:44,792
Talk to me. Come on, tell me why.

791
01:23:46,476 --> 01:23:49,035
Well, now you have nothing to say, huh?

792
01:23:49,472 --> 01:23:51,435
Talk to me! Say something!

793
01:23:54,309 --> 01:23:55,722
Then kiss me.

794
01:24:42,354 --> 01:24:44,721
Kate? Kate.

795
01:25:50,638 --> 01:25:52,668
Thomas! Thomas!

796
01:27:53,416 --> 01:27:56,928
Good god, Alex. What happened?

797
01:27:59,044 --> 01:28:00,580
Stevens is dead.

798
01:28:01,610 --> 01:28:02,855
Vaughn Stevens?

799
01:28:03,255 --> 01:28:07,003
- Baldwin's dead, too.
- Baldwin? Who is Baldwin?

800
01:28:07,105 --> 01:28:08,519
What are you talking about?

801
01:28:08,619 --> 01:28:13,354
There's no political motivation,
no financial motivation.

802
01:28:16,123 --> 01:28:18,984
The only motivation I see is a personal one.

803
01:28:19,348 --> 01:28:22,792
- Why bring this to me?
- Because I need to know the truth.

804
01:28:24,875 --> 01:28:26,749
Like I told you before.

805
01:28:27,509 --> 01:28:28,686
You're too close.

806
01:28:28,792 --> 01:28:29,835
You can't see it.

807
01:28:29,944 --> 01:28:32,008
You have to see it
from the right perspective.

808
01:28:32,115 --> 01:28:33,462
Right perspective. Perspective.

809
01:28:33,563 --> 01:28:35,403
Try mine. Perspective.

810
01:28:48,800 --> 01:28:52,615
If you can't see it, Alex,
then you're still too close.

811
01:28:54,691 --> 01:28:56,037
Not anymore.

812
01:28:57,783 --> 01:28:58,927
Good.

813
01:29:01,140 --> 01:29:02,878
Then you understand.

814
01:29:04,990 --> 01:29:08,535
There's nothing you can do.
You have no proof.

815
01:29:09,894 --> 01:29:12,688
It was always your job to keep his secret.

816
01:29:13,776 --> 01:29:16,143
I just want the President to be...

817
01:29:16,706 --> 01:29:18,669
remembered as a good President.

818
01:29:18,779 --> 01:29:20,618
Still protecting him, huh?

819
01:29:23,057 --> 01:29:24,594
It's over, Alex.

820
01:30:11,036 --> 01:30:13,526
- Wow, you clean up real good.
- Why, thank you.

821
01:30:13,636 --> 01:30:16,497
- You look very handsome yourself.
- Thank you.

822
01:30:18,111 --> 01:30:21,365
Took the liberty of ordering us
a bottle of wine.

823
01:30:22,225 --> 01:30:23,795
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

824
01:30:25,219 --> 01:30:26,397
No ring.

825
01:30:27,885 --> 01:30:30,252
You know, this isn't a date-date.

826
01:30:32,262 --> 01:30:35,740
- You think I'd date you?
- Like you'd ever get the chance.

827
01:30:36,935 --> 01:30:39,627
- Unless.
- Unless?

828
01:30:39,896 --> 01:30:43,509
Unless you tell me
what really happened with Stevens.

829
01:30:44,240 --> 01:30:47,325
The whole story.
Because suicide is just too easy.

830
01:30:48,353 --> 01:30:52,258
Well, with Baldwin still alive,
he could've been tied in to the whole thing.

831
01:30:52,368 --> 01:30:55,914
It's just a matter of time.
So, he took the easy way out.

832
01:30:56,054 --> 01:30:58,421
But why do it in the first place?

833
01:30:59,772 --> 01:31:02,464
I don't know.
We're still looking for a motive.

834
01:31:02,569 --> 01:31:04,802
And what if you don't find one?

835
01:31:08,460 --> 01:31:10,726
What then, you're just gonna walk away?

836
01:31:10,829 --> 01:31:13,847
Far enough to see things
from a different perspective.

837
01:31:14,548 --> 01:31:17,566
- That's it?
- Unless you know something I don't.

838
01:31:17,674 --> 01:31:18,852
- Thomas, I don't believe it.
- What?

839
01:31:18,957 --> 01:31:20,528
After everything that we've been through...

840
01:31:20,636 --> 01:31:24,541
after everything that's happened to us,
you're still holding out on me?

841
01:31:27,020 --> 01:31:30,038
Fine. All right, well,
you know I won't give up.

842
01:31:30,573 --> 01:31:33,199
I'm not the woman that just walks away.

843
01:31:34,786 --> 01:31:38,174
Now, I will find out the truth. I will.

844
01:31:38,274 --> 01:31:40,372
- To the truth.
- To the truth.

